article.headline: Lafayette 85, Duquesne 71
article.story: PITTSBURGH (AP) -- Marcus Harley scored 19 points, 14 in the first half, as Lafayette beat Duquesne 85-71 on Saturday. Harley hit four 3-pointers in a two-minute span to give Lafayette a 14-11 lead with 14:28 left in the first half. The Dukes and Leopards (1-0) traded the lead until Andrei Capusan's jump shot gave Lafayette the lead for good with 7:09 to play in the first half. The Leopards shot 51 percent (25 of 59) from the floor and made 9-of-19 3-point attempts, while the Dukes managed only 34.8 percent (24 of 69) and were 6-of-21 from 3-point range. Sean Knitter scored 12 of his 14 points in the second half for Lafayette while Jamaal Hilliard added 15 and went 10-for-10 from the free-throw line. Bryant McAllister scored a career-high 24 points for Duquesne, while Martin Osimani added 16. Kieron Achara had his second double-double of the season with 11 points and 10 rebounds for the Dukes.
